00:40:04,938 --> 00:40:07,141
Especially when everything's calm, everything's peaceful.

401
00:40:07,161 --> 00:40:08,063
That's the time to do it.

402
00:40:08,103 --> 00:40:10,449
You can't do it when you're raging.

403
00:40:10,469 --> 00:40:11,710
So when you're calm, when you're peaceful.

404
00:40:11,731 --> 00:40:12,351
This is what I mean.

405
00:40:12,713 --> 00:40:19,385
The more beautiful we become in our ethical life, the more beautiful our hearts become, the easier it is to drop the self.

406
00:40:20,715 --> 00:40:24,422
So when everything is peaceful, it doesn't have to be in a sitting posture.

407
00:40:24,601 --> 00:40:26,565
You could be sitting in an armchair at home.

408
00:40:26,585 --> 00:40:28,168
You could be walking in nature.

409
00:40:28,809 --> 00:40:42,471
But as soon as you get that sense of being within yourself, being the observer, the one who knows, you see, just stop for a moment, you see, and just feel that sense of presence because it's a mirror image.

410
00:40:42,490 --> 00:40:43,132
It's a mirror image.

411
00:40:46,237 --> 00:40:47,179
And just see if you can,

412
00:40:50,230 --> 00:41:20,135
made of what's in the knowing what's it made of now as far as we're concerned as human beings we're made of three things we're made of the mind which expresses itself in thoughts and images we're made of a heart which is expressed in emotions and mood I'm using it as an emotional heart and we're made of the body and the only thing we know of the body is sensations and feelings sensations and feelings

413
00:41:21,836 --> 00:41:27,626
Can you find any of that within the observer?

414
00:41:27,646 --> 00:41:35,978
So these are things that you can actually begin to question when you're in that very clear state of the observer, the feeler, the one who knows.

415
00:41:37,681 --> 00:41:49,380
And what that's beginning to do for us is to clarify, is to begin to clarify for us where this state that the Buddha's talking about, this nirvanic state is to be found.

416
00:41:50,862 --> 00:41:53,867
And the more we'll be drawn there, the more that we'll be drawn there.

417
00:41:53,887 --> 00:41:56,692
And the more you're drawn there, the more you're drawn to silence.

418
00:41:57,393 --> 00:42:01,139
The more you're drawn to peacefulness.

419
00:42:01,159 --> 00:42:11,677
Of course, you have to be careful that you then don't get into a sort of quietism where you just want to sit there, you know, anonymous under a tree or something.

420
00:42:11,697 --> 00:42:14,121
It also has to be that outflow of wisdom.

421
00:42:14,561 --> 00:42:16,244
And that's exactly what happened to the Buddha.

422
00:42:16,782 --> 00:42:21,869
So he attained this state, and it must have been quite amazing to him.

423
00:42:21,889 --> 00:42:24,353
He must have thought, what is it?

424
00:42:24,474 --> 00:42:29,862
I mean, he had to investigate the state that he'd actually found himself in, this liberation.

425
00:42:29,882 --> 00:42:30,762
He hadn't come across it.

426
00:42:31,324 --> 00:42:32,867
Nobody had talked about it.

427
00:42:33,206 --> 00:42:34,027
He didn't know anything about it.

428
00:42:34,047 --> 00:42:37,693
He had to actually investigate this state of being in Nirvana.

429
00:42:38,996 --> 00:42:43,583
And it's when he investigates that, and he investigates how he used to suffer,

430
00:42:44,052 --> 00:42:46,293
And how he overcame that suffering.

431
00:42:46,313 --> 00:42:51,360
And that's the psychology that we call dependent origination.

432
00:42:51,380 --> 00:42:58,568
And as soon as that happened, as soon as he gathered that, the desire to share it was quite natural.

433
00:42:59,449 --> 00:43:01,210
Because it's no longer about him.

434
00:43:03,333 --> 00:43:06,755
So then he thinks the memory of his two teachers come up.

435
00:43:06,775 --> 00:43:08,958
And they both died.

436
00:43:09,018 --> 00:43:11,702
So there's a sense of sorrow about that.

437
00:43:12,101 --> 00:43:13,923
Do not confuse sorrow with grief.

438
00:43:15,001 --> 00:43:22,228
Sorrow is a very pure state where you're resonating with somebody else's suffering.

439
00:43:22,248 --> 00:43:27,835
And the sorrow has to express itself in some compassionate way, even if it's only sending a good wish.

440
00:43:28,777 --> 00:43:37,668
Otherwise it remains unrequited and can slip into a sense of grief, a sense of unworthiness because you didn't do anything.

441
00:43:37,688 --> 00:43:39,809
So you have to be quite careful about that.

442
00:43:41,123 --> 00:43:49,547
So in that sort of investigation, we're getting close, we're beginning to perceive what the Buddha means by it.

443
00:43:50,724 --> 00:43:55,331
And when you're in that state, you begin to perceive it as a better state to be in.

444
00:43:55,373 --> 00:43:58,538
A better state to be in awareness than to be in non-aware.

445
00:43:59,780 --> 00:44:05,509
Even though, you know, it's sort of creating an enormous pain in the back, in the knees, in the neck.

446
00:44:06,269 --> 00:44:09,375
All this stuff's coming up.

447
00:44:09,596 --> 00:44:17,188
There's a sort of feeling that, well, even in this horror, it's better to be aware than to go around like a monkey.

448
00:44:20,273 --> 00:44:21,474
Let me just see.

449
00:44:23,177 --> 00:44:25,039
Can you turn the lights on?

450
00:44:25,239 --> 00:44:41,237
I'm beginning to talk to the darkness.

451
00:44:41,778 --> 00:44:46,824
I just like to end by pointing out something that's been happening, I think, to a lot of people.

452
00:44:47,405 --> 00:44:49,909
All this business around

453
00:44:50,293 --> 00:45:08,123
Isis and and the Islamic thing and all the horror stories that are coming out today and how people can I know feel overwhelmed by the horrors of it you see remember we You have to be careful with yourself.

454
00:45:08,143 --> 00:45:10,007
You know not go beyond what's possible

455
00:45:11,067 --> 00:45:15,675
Remember that there's two, you might say, two rings of power around us.

456
00:45:15,775 --> 00:45:18,079
The first one is what I can do.

457
00:45:18,119 --> 00:45:27,557
Very little anybody can do about what's happening in the Middle East, either around Palestine or around what's happening to ISIS.

458
00:45:27,657 --> 00:45:29,822
Very little that you can actually do.

459
00:45:30,583 --> 00:45:33,750
The next part is the influence, what you can get other people to do.

460
00:45:34,269 --> 00:45:37,552
And it might be, you know, writing letters, whatever.

461
00:45:38,173 --> 00:45:40,215
There might be something that can be done there.

462
00:45:40,536 --> 00:45:44,139
But beyond that, if you try and get beyond that, all you're going to do is exhaust yourself.

463
00:45:44,159 --> 00:45:51,588
You're just going to get yourself into an absolute state of feeling, you know, disempowered and all that sort of stuff.

464
00:45:51,608 --> 00:45:54,710
And the fact is that you think that that's false, but you are disempowered.

465
00:45:54,731 --> 00:45:57,875
You can only do certain things.

466
00:45:57,894 --> 00:46:00,177
So the final thing you can do is at least send good wishes.

467
00:46:01,152 --> 00:46:07,257
Now, it might be that you don't believe that your thought patterns can actually help other people in other places.

468
00:46:07,617 --> 00:46:14,684
But at least it's doing something within you to create a proper relationship to the situation that you find yourself in.

469
00:46:14,704 --> 00:46:19,128
Just on that note, I have a friend in the Alabama who teaches dowsing.

470
00:46:19,748 --> 00:46:29,876
And one of the things he does is he gets two people on both sides of the room to send a thought to each other, a blessing or something like that, if you know what I mean.

471
00:46:30,210 --> 00:46:32,576
And they all douse that line, that energy line.

472
00:46:32,996 --> 00:46:36,382
And he says they can douse it for six weeks.

473
00:46:36,402 --> 00:46:39,208
They can feel that energy in the line for six weeks.

474
00:46:40,351 --> 00:46:43,536
It's an aboriginal song, what do they call it?

475
00:46:43,556 --> 00:46:44,798
Aboriginal song line.

476
00:46:44,818 --> 00:46:45,760
Song line, yeah.

477
00:46:46,501 --> 00:46:49,467
So without getting too mystical about it,

478
00:46:50,527 --> 00:46:57,047
There is a point where you can say to yourself, well, I know enough about this situation.

479
00:46:57,067 --> 00:46:59,454
I don't have to keep feeding it with these images.

480
00:46:59,996 --> 00:47:01,500
Sometimes you can turn the news off.

481
00:47:02,864 --> 00:47:05,829
You know, just keep feeding the same old bad story.

482
00:47:06,289 --> 00:47:08,634
Well, we know what's going on, and what can we do?

483
00:47:08,833 --> 00:47:14,744
Well, at least I might be able to write a letter or send a goodwill or do something, you know.

484
00:47:15,164 --> 00:47:21,215
But just to find ourselves completely disempowered is just overreaching what we can do.

485
00:47:21,615 --> 00:47:25,943
And in a sense, it's a lack of humility, isn't it?

486
00:47:25,963 --> 00:47:27,264
You can do more than you can.

487
00:47:27,284 --> 00:47:28,246
There's a sort of pride in it.

488
00:47:30,590 --> 00:47:35,507
So just in case you found yourself being quite upset about things that are happening around the world.

489
00:47:35,887 --> 00:47:37,514
The Pope's called it Third World War.

490
00:47:37,534 --> 00:47:41,186
He's close on the beginning of a Third World War.

491
00:47:42,088 --> 00:47:42,590
It's pretty miserable.

492
00:47:43,954 --> 00:47:52,686
So on that happy note, remember that there's two sides to our practice, you see, remember that.

493
00:47:52,706 --> 00:48:07,228
There's the side which is to do with ethics, which is to do with relationships, which is to do with letting go of all that selfishness and anger and all that sort of, and really a positive effort to develop goodwill, compassion, joy,

494
00:48:07,208 --> 00:48:20,766
And as we're doing that, we're doing this investigation into impermanence, into the process of this wrong desire, really begin to see that.

495
00:48:21,568 --> 00:48:25,873
And the fact that when it remains only as a desire, nothing's happened.

496
00:48:26,273 --> 00:48:27,315
It has to be willed.

497
00:48:28,197 --> 00:48:35,106
There has to be an action which takes it into a pattern of thought, or a pattern of speech, or an action.

498
00:48:39,608 --> 00:48:42,251
And this business of not me, not mine, you see.

499
00:48:43,092 --> 00:48:44,554
So that's not a negativity.

500
00:48:44,594 --> 00:48:46,137
There is nothing.

501
00:48:47,117 --> 00:48:52,644
It's actually a way of investigating this whole problem of identity.

502
00:48:53,786 --> 00:48:54,106
Okay.

503
00:49:00,614 --> 00:49:02,338
So I'll leave a piece of paper there.

504
00:49:02,998 --> 00:49:07,945
Might be time to ask some questions, clarifications tomorrow afternoon.

505
00:49:09,864 --> 00:49:13,231
I can only hope my words have been of some assistance.

506
00:49:13,873 --> 00:49:29,206
May you, by your fierce commitment to the practice and devotion to love, compassion, joy and peace and all the rest of it, attain full liberation sooner rather

507
00:49:35,077 --> 00:49:48,300
So use this, just see what your state is, whether it's just a matter of relaxing and breathing in the night air and doing something like that, or doing some walking meditation.

508
00:49:49,822 --> 00:49:54,931
And then we'll come back and do the last session of the evening, you see.

509
00:49:54,952 --> 00:49:59,699
But the important thing is to get in the habit of not allowing the mind to wander.

510
00:50:01,012 --> 00:50:03,516
There's no rest.

511
00:50:03,918 --> 00:50:05,820
You can't take a holiday in the spiritual life.

512
00:50:06,963 --> 00:50:11,050
You can't say, well, today I'm just going to go berserk.

513
00:50:12,833 --> 00:50:14,094
Sex, drugs and rock and roll.

514
00:50:15,376 --> 00:50:18,481
It's like once you're in there, you're in, you're locked in.

515
00:50:20,909 --> 00:50:32,581
And not to expect big things, not to expect some huge out-of-this-world bomb that's going to break and suddenly become floating angels or something.

516
00:50:32,601 --> 00:50:40,710
The process is very slow, and the Buddha's call is about gradual, a gradual training, you see.

517
00:50:40,731 --> 00:50:43,815
It ruins the sex, drugs, and rock and roll, doesn't it?

518
00:50:43,835 --> 00:50:43,954
Sorry?

519
00:50:43,974 --> 00:50:45,556
It sort of ruins the sex, drugs, and rock and roll.

520
00:50:45,577 --> 00:50:46,498
Well, this is it, you see.

521
00:50:47,298 --> 00:50:48,519
It takes the joy out of life.

522
00:50:54,389 --> 00:50:55,168
Very good.

